Hypothesis: There is no difference in directional specific manipulation of the thoracic spine for patients with neck pain.

 Patients seeking physical therapy for neck pain routinely have their thoracic spine manipulated.

 This study seeks to determine if directional limitations in the spine can be specifically determined and treated to decrease neck pain.

